Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler or #grill{} to high. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into 1-inch-thick wedges. Finely mince 1 wedge. Zest @lemon{1} until you have 1 tsp zest, then cut into wedges. Halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise. Slice each half into long, thin wedges. Halve @grape tomatoes{4}. Pick @basil{1/2%bunch} leaves from stems; discard stems. Thinly slice leaves.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{4%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add minced onion and @Israeli couscous{1/2%cup}. Cook, tossing, until onion is softened and couscous lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Pour in 1 cup water and @veggie stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a boil, then lower heat, reduce to a simmer, and cover. Cook until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Toss zucchini, onion wedges, @sumac{1%tsp}, and a large drizzle of olive oil on a #baking sheet{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Broil until lightly charred, ~{10-15%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

> TIP: If using grill, place oiled and seasoned zucchini and onion over direct heat and grill until tender, 10-15 minutes, turning occasionally.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Take 4 oz (about half) of the @grilling cheese{4%oz} and cut it into 2 large slices. Place @za'atar{1%tbsp} on a #plate{}. Press cheese into za'atar to evenly coat all over. Add to pan and cook until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If grilling, place cheese on grates and grill until browned, 2-3 minutes per side.

Once couscous is done, transfer to a #large bowl{}. Stir in tomatoes, half the basil, a squeeze of lemon juice, and lemon zest. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide couscous between plates. Top with zucchini, onion, and grilling cheese. Garnish with remaining basil and serve with lemon wedges on the side for squeezing over.